  "body": "#### Description\r\nSame as https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/issues/4755 (maybe it's leftover case just for when in block `0x0` transactions) \r\n\r\neth_getBlockTransactionCountByHash & eth_getBlockTransactionCountByNumber return null when block didn't have any transaction. \r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2.37.0\r\nOS & Version: Linux \r\nChain/Network: Confirmed with ETH Mainnet, Gnosis Mainnet \r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"id\": 1,\r\n    \"result\": \"0x0\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\n{\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"id\": 1,\r\n    \"result\": null\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST 'ERIGON_NODE_URL' \\\r\n-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n--data'{\r\n    \"id\": 1,\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"method\": \"eth_getBlockTransactionCountByNumber\",\r\n    \"params\": [\r\n        \"0xABCD0\"\r\n    ]\r\n}'\r\n\r\n```\r\nor (block hash value for above request) \r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST 'ERIGON_NODE_URL' \\\r\n-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\r\n--data'{\r\n    \"id\": 1,\r\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n    \"method\": \"eth_getBlockTransactionCountByHash\",\r\n    \"params\": [\r\n        \"0xc807840fef2e24a5213681a4895aca9390bb7b188f33a0d44e22221b84a8a4f0\"\r\n    ]\r\n}'\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
